NAME
    gcloud alpha ml products reference-images add - add a Cloud Product Search
        ReferenceImage to a Catalog

SYNOPSIS
    gcloud alpha ml products reference-images add IMAGE_PATH --catalog=CATALOG
        --product-id=PRODUCT_ID
        [--bounds=x:y,x:y,x:y,[x:y,...] --category=CATEGORY]
        [GCLOUD_WIDE_FLAG ...]

DESCRIPTION
    (ALPHA) This command creates a Cloud Product Search ReferenceImage and adds
    it to the provided catalog.

POSITIONAL ARGUMENTS
     IMAGE_PATH
        The Google Cloud Storage URI of the input image file. The URI must
        start with gs://.

REQUIRED FLAGS
     --catalog=CATALOG
        The catalog to add ReferenceImages to.

     --product-id=PRODUCT_ID
        The product ID to associate this ReferenceImage to. Product Id is
        restricted to 255 characters including letters, numbers, underscore ( _
        ) and hyphen (-).

OPTIONAL FLAGS
     Both --category and --bounds should be specified if either is provided.

       --bounds=x:y,x:y,x:y,[x:y,...]
          A set of vertices defining the bounding polygon aroundthe area of
          interest in the image. Should be a list of integer pairs, separated
          by commas specifying the vertices (e.g. [x1:y2,
          x2:y2,x3:y3...xn:yn]). Defaults to full image if empty.

       --category=CATEGORY
          String specifying the product category to associate this
          ReferenceImage to.

GCLOUD WIDE FLAGS
    These flags are available to all commands: --account, --configuration,
    --flatten, --format, --help, --log-http, --project, --quiet, --trace-token,
    --user-output-enabled, --verbosity. Run $ gcloud help for details.

EXAMPLES
    To create a reference image, using default bounds and no category, run:

        $ gcloud alpha ml products reference-images add \
        gs:\\my-bucket\myimage.jpg
        --catalog=101
        --product-id=my-product-123

    To add a reference image, using custom bounds and category, run:

        $ gcloud alpha ml products reference-images add \
        gs:\\my-bucket\myimage.jpg
        --catalog=101
        --product-id=my-product-123
        --category=mens_shoes
        --bounds=200:200,200:400,400:200,400:400

    Note: For alpha, only catalogs with associated ReferenceImages will be
    displayed by the list command. Please be sure to note the catalog name at
    creation time so that it can be used by ml products catalogs
    reference-image commands.

NOTES
    This command is currently in ALPHA and may change without notice. Usually,
    users of ALPHA commands and flags need to apply for access, agree to
    applicable terms, and have their projects whitelisted. Contact Google or
    sign up on a product's page for ALPHA access. Product pages can be found at
    https://cloud.google.com/products/.

